# ─────────────────────────── Rust / Cargo ───────────────────────────
/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Cargo.lock IS tracked here — usta is a binary, not a library, so the
# lockfile guarantees reproducible builds. (For library-only crates we'd
# add `Cargo.lock` here.)

# proptest regressions IS tracked — failing inputs become permanent
# regression tests on the property tests. See:
#   https://altsysrq.github.io/proptest-book/proptest/failure-persistence.html

# ─────────────────────────── Secrets ────────────────────────────────
# Anything with a credential, key, or token. Be paranoid here.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.crt
*.pfx
*.kdbx
secrets/
.cargo/credentials.toml
.cargo/credentials

# ─────────────────────────── Editors / IDEs ─────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
.fleet/
.zed/
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.orig
*~

# ─────────────────────────── OS noise ───────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ─────────────────────────── Tooling caches ─────────────────────────
.direnv/
.cache/
.fleet/

# Coverage outputs (cargo-llvm-cov, tarpaulin, etc.)
*.profraw
*.profdata
coverage/
tarpaulin-report.html
cobertura.xml
lcov.info

# Profiling outputs
flamegraph.svg
perf.data
perf.data.old
*.dSYM/

# ─────────────────────────── Logs ───────────────────────────────────
*.log

# ─────────────────────────── Local usta state ───────────────────────
# `.usta/` here would only appear if someone scaffolds INTO this repo
# by mistake (e.g. `usta new my-app` from the repo root). The ignore
# protects us from accidentally committing scaffold output.
#
# In *generated projects*, `.usta/` is intentionally tracked (see the
# nx-monorepo template's base/.gitignore, which uses `!.usta/`).
.usta/

# Per-user local overrides
*.local

# Generated test fixtures (ad-hoc — vast majority of tests use tempfile)
/tests/tmp/


.claude/
